---
title: Discover the Best Free Browser Games
description: Discover the best free browser games on ArcadeBloom. Browse action, puzzle, arcade and strategy games by category, read honest reviews, and play at the source.
permalink: /
---
{# Homepage — editorial directory style.
   Hero (merged with page, no colliding gradient panel) → asymmetric Editor's
   Picks → Browse by Category (list rows) → New Arrivals (horizontal rail) →
   About (prose column). Preserves all URLs, categories, JSON-LD, business
   positioning. Static pre-rendered, no JS-rendered rails. #}

{% extends 'base.njk' %}

{% set featured_games = games | featuredOnly | limit(8) %}
{% set new_games = games | sortByDateDesc | limit(12) %}
{% set total_games = games | length %}

{% block jsonld %}
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@type": "WebSite",
      "name": "ArcadeBloom",
      "description": "{{ site.description }}",
      "url": "{{ site.url }}/",
      "publisher": { "@id": "{{ site.url }}/#org" },
      "potentialAction": {
        "@type": "SearchAction",
        "target": {
          "@type": "EntryPoint",
          "urlTemplate": "{{ site.url }}/search/?q={search_term_string}"
        },
        "query-input": "required name=search_term_string"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "@id": "{{ site.url }}/#org",
      "name": "ArcadeBloom",
      "url": "{{ site.url }}/",
      "description": "A curated directory of free browser games.",
      "logo": "{{ site.url }}/og-image.png"
    }
  ]
}
</script>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
{# =====================================================================
   HERO — merged with the page, no separate colliding gradient panel.
   Eyebrow + two-line display H1 + value prop + search + CTA.
   ===================================================================== #}
<section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-12 pb-10 md:pt-20 md:pb-14">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="eyebrow mb-5">
            <span class="text-bloom">●</span> est. 2026 · {{ total_games | number }} games catalogued
        </p>
        <h1 class="display-h1 text-[2.5rem] leading-[1.05] sm:text-6xl lg:text-7xl">
            Discover the best<br>
            free <span class="text-bloom">browser games</span>.
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg md:text-xl text-paper-70 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
            A curated directory of free web games — no installs, no walled garden.
            Read the review, then play at the source.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 sm:items-center max-w-2xl">
            <div class="flex-1">
                {% set size = 'lg' %}
                {% include 'search-inline.njk' %}
            </div>
            <a href="#picks" class="btn-ghost shrink-0">Browse picks</a>
        </div>

        {# Category color strip — thin row of all six categories at a glance.
           Gives instant visual identity to the taxonomy. #}
        <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-4 gap-y-2 text-sm">
            <span class="eyebrow !text-xs mr-1">Browse</span>
            {% for cat in site.categories %}
            {% set cat_count = games | whereEq('category', cat.slug) | length %}
            <a href="/category/{{ cat.slug }}/" class="cat-{{ cat.slug }} inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-paper-70 hover:text-bloom transition-colors">
                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[var(--cat)]"></span>
                {{ cat.name }}
                <span class="font-mono text-xs text-paper-45">{{ cat_count }}</span>
            </a>
            {% endfor %}
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

{# =====================================================================
   EDITOR'S PICKS — asymmetric layout, not a uniform grid.
   1 large feature (first pick) + a row of smaller satellites.
   Signals editorial curation rather than a product catalog.
   ===================================================================== #}
{% set picks = featured_games | sortByScreenshotThenDate | limit(7) %}
{% if picks.length %}
<section id="picks" class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-10 md:py-14">
    {% set heading_eyebrow = "Editor's picks" %}
    {% set heading_title = "Jump straight in" %}
    {% set heading_subtitle = "Award-winning browser games, hand-picked. Read the review, then play at the source." %}
    {% set heading_href = "/featured/" %}
    {% set heading_link_label = "All featured" %}
    {% include 'section-heading.njk' %}
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-4 md:gap-6">
        {# Hero feature — first pick, spans tall on large screens #}
        {% if picks.length > 0 %}
        {% set game = picks[0] %}
        {% set lazy = false %}
        <div class="lg:row-span-2">
            {% include 'game-card-feature.njk' %}
        </div>
        {% endif %}

        {# Satellites — the rest, in a responsive sub-grid #}
        {% set satellites = picks | slice(1, 6) %}
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 md:gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3">
            {% for game in satellites %}
            {% include 'game-card.njk' %}
            {% endfor %}
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-6 sm:hidden">
        <a href="/featured/" class="btn-ghost w-full">All featured picks →</a>
    </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

{# Sponsored slot — contained visually (label + hairline) so it reads as
   intentional rather than a broken widget. #}
<div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    {% include 'ad-banner.njk' %}
</div>

{# =====================================================================
   BROWSE BY CATEGORY — editorial list rows, not cards.
   Each row carries its category accent on hover.
   ===================================================================== #}
<section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 md:py-20">
    {% set heading_eyebrow = 'The catalogue' %}
    {% set heading_title = 'Browse by Category' %}
    {% set heading_subtitle = 'Six top-level categories covering every kind of browser game we catalogue.' %}
    {% include 'section-heading.njk' %}
    <div class="border-b border-[var(--hairline)]">
        {% for cat in site.categories %}
        {% set cat_count = games | whereEq('category', cat.slug) | length %}
        {% set is_thin = cat_count < site.minGamesPerCategory %}
        {% set count = cat_count %}
        {% set min = site.minGamesPerCategory %}
        {% include 'category-row.njk' %}
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
</section>

{# =====================================================================
   NEW ARRIVALS — horizontal scroll rail.
   Differentiated from Editor's Picks: peek/scroll says "fresh, keep moving".
   ===================================================================== #}
{% if new_games.length %}
<section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-10 md:py-14">
    {% set heading_eyebrow = 'Fresh in' %}
    {% set heading_title = 'New arrivals' %}
    {% set heading_subtitle = 'The most recent additions to the directory.' %}
    {% include 'section-heading.njk' %}
    {# The rail is one row of cards; on small screens each card is ~70vw,
       on md+ a fixed 260px. Snap scrolling keeps it tidy. #}
    <div class="rail -mx-4 px-4 sm:mx-0 sm:px-0">
        {% for game in new_games %}
        <div class="w-[70vw] sm:w-[260px]">
            {% include 'game-card.njk' %}
        </div>
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
    <div class="mt-5">
        <a href="/new/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-semibold text-bloom hover:text-paper transition-colors">
            See all new arrivals <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
    </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

{# =====================================================================
   ABOUT — editorial prose column (max-w-prose feel).
   Reinforces topical relevance for "browser games / web games / game
   directory" with real internal links, no glass card.
   ===================================================================== #}
<section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <p class="eyebrow mb-3">About</p>
        <h2 class="display-h2 text-3xl md:text-4xl">A directory, not a portal.</h2>
        <div class="text-paper-70 leading-relaxed space-y-5 mt-6 text-lg">
            <p>
                ArcadeBloom is a curated directory of
                <strong class="text-paper">free browser games</strong> — no downloads, no installs,
                no walled garden. We catalogue the best <strong class="text-paper">web games</strong>
                from across the internet: open-source projects on GitHub, indie titles on personal
                sites, and competition entries from events like js13kGames. Every game links out to
                its original author's site, so you always play the real thing where it lives.
            </p>
            <p>
                Browse <a href="/category/puzzle/" class="link-inline">puzzle games</a> for logic and
                number challenges, <a href="/category/arcade/" class="link-inline">arcade games</a>
                for retro and score-attack fun, <a href="/category/action/" class="link-inline">action games</a>
                for reflex-driven shooters, or <a href="/category/strategy/" class="link-inline">strategy games</a>
                when you want to plan before you move. Each entry comes with an honest review, a
                how-to-play guide, and transparent source attribution.
            </p>
            <p>
                Unlike portals that re-host other people's work, ArcadeBloom is a
                <strong class="text-paper">game directory</strong>: we discover, review, and link.
                That means cleaner licensing, fairer credit to creators, and a catalogue you can
                trust. New <strong class="text-paper">free online games</strong> are added regularly
                — bookmark this page or check the <a href="/new/" class="link-inline">latest additions</a>.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
{% endblock %}
